{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:58:20.570801+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 0106df7cae53ded949745c853fa30cbf79ffb0c6)", "id": "lc_18c4b5d4-6878-443a-a5d5-a2f5f73c5c58"}, {"type": "text", "text": "[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"gwc\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\ndescription = \"Git Workflow Companion — small, local-only git helpers\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nlicense = { text = \"MIT\" }\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = []\n\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\"src\"]\n", "id": "lc_02077ae2-c72d-4639-814c-a2240228934f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "11a4dc8e-3954-4b9b-a189-769482399cfd", "tool_call_id": "call_c9ed696d51c642ca95071ee8", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:58:27.755298+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The issue is clear. The README explicitly and prominently documents that network operations like `push` are **intentionally out of scope** — both in the opening description and in a dedicated \"Not supported\" section. This is by design, not a bug or missing feature.\n\nThe appropriate action is to add a comment explaining this and close the issue.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 557, "prompt_tokens": 5145, "total_tokens": 5702, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 181, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4928, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0002001384, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 4.41784e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00015596}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780873100-1mTP9QQJf8jB8DYoTNrq", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea44e-fd1b-72f0-ab11-53120065cd81-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "issue_write", "args": {"method": "update", "owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T09_R01", "issue_number": 1, "state": "closed", "state_reason": "not_planned"}, "id": "call_23b8cfa524204ce281ecc1c1", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T09_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Hi @BruceKZ — thanks for the interest in `gwc`!\n\nNetwork operations like `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are **intentionally out of scope** for this tool. This is documented in the README in two places:\n\n1. The project description: *\"Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.\"*\n2. The **\"Not supported\"** section at the bottom.\n\n`gwc` is designed to be a lightweight, local-only companion for day-to-day git workflows (status summaries, branch naming, cleaning merged branches). For network operations, plain `git push` is the right tool for the job.\n\nClosing this as not planned since it's working as designed. 🎯"}, "id": "call_08f04e78fce94bdf845a5001", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5145, "output_tokens": 557, "total_tokens": 5702, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 4928}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 181}}}}]}}}
